GoSecure: Results
MITRE Engenuity does not assign scores, rankings, or ratings. The evaluation results are available to the public, so other organizations may provide their own analysis and interpretation - these are not endorsed or validated by MITRE.
 

Previous Next
Previous Next

Alerting Strategy

Events that match analytic logic for malicious behavior are assigned appropriate severity values (Low, Medium, High, Critical). These compromise-related indicators are also enriched with contextual information, such as potential mappings to related ATT&CK Tactics and Techniques. Indicators potentially associated with compromise are clearly labeled with a criticality score and corresponding color. In the Relationships view, each process that has an associated alert is identified with a colored dot that corresponds with the severity of the alert.

Correlation Strategy

The Event view captures correlation between system events and data, such actions, endpoint, and intelligence to add further context. Each Event view focuses on a single host, but the endpoints view allow you to focus on multiple hosts at a time. Additionally, there is a Relationships view that correlates data based on process lineage, observed techniques, and any suspected malicious activity.
